 Systems Analysis), , Moscow: Nauka; Rubinshtein, E.S., Polozova, L.G., (1966) Sovremennye izmeneniya klimata (Current Climate Changes), , Leningrad: Gidrometeoizdat; Sirotenko, O.D., Gruza, G.V., Ran'kova, E.Y., Current Climate Changes in Heat Availability, Moisture Abundance, and Productivity of the Russian Agrsphere (2007) Meteorol. Gidrol., (8), pp. 90-103; (2001) Sostoyanie i kompleksnyi monitoring prirodnoi sredy i klimata. Predely izmenenii (The State and Multidisciplinary Monitoring of the Environment and Climate), , Yu. A. Izrael' (Ed.), Moscow: Nauka; Sochava, V.B., Bachurin, G.V., Krauklis, A.A., Nechaeva, E.G., Topological Features of Heat and Moisture in Taiga Geosystems (1970) Dokl. Inst. Geografii Sibiri I Dal'nego Vostoka, (26), pp. 39-53; Tarko, A.M., (2005) Antropogennye izmeneniya global'nykh biosfernykh protsessov. Matematicheskoe modelirovanie (Anthropogenic Changes in Global Biospheric Processes: Mathematical Modeling), , Moscow: Fizmatlit; (1964) Fiziko-geograficheskoe raionirovanie Srednego Povolzh'ya (Physico-Geographical Zoning of Middle Volga Region), , A. V. Stupishin (Ed.), Kazan: Izd. Kazan. Gos. Univ; (1996) Climate Change 1995. The Science of Climatic Change, , J. T. Houghton, FilhoL. G. Meira, and B. A. Callander (Eds.), Cambridge: Cambridge Univ. Press; Gordon, C., Cooper, C., Senior, C.A., The Simulation of SST, Sea Ice Extents and Ocean Heat Transport in a Version of the Hadley Centre Coupled Model Without Flux Adjustments (2000) Clim. Dyn., 16 (1), pp. 147-168; Hansen, J.G., Hung, I., Lasis, A., Global Climate Changes as Forecasted by Goddard Institute for Space Studies Three-Dimensional Models (1988) J. Geophys. Res., 92, pp. 9341-9354; Pope, V.D., Gallani, M.L., Rowntree, P.R., Stratton, R.A., The Impact of New Physical Parameterizations in Hadley Centre Climate Model-HadCM3 (2000) Clim. Dyn., 16, pp. 123-146; Santer, B., The Use General Circulation Models in Climate Impact Analysis-A Preliminary Stay of the Impacts of a CO2-In